title Risk Management Across the Financial Services Landscape

// OWM coordinate convention: [visibility, maturity]
// visibility 0 = bottom of map, 1 = top (closest to user)
// maturity   0 = Genesis, 1 = Commodity

// Anchors (users with demand for financial services risk management) — top-right
component Public [0.97, 0.88]
component Corporations [0.95, 0.86]
component Governments [0.93, 0.80]

// Providers (delivering financial services against demand) — high visibility, commodity
component Retail Banking [0.85, 0.80]
component Insurance [0.80, 0.78]
component Lending [0.82, 0.76]

// Trust and assets layer (intermediating surface between providers and customers)
component Trust [0.70, 0.70]
component Assets [0.78, 0.68]
component Customer Relationship [0.72, 0.72]

// Risk types covered by risk management
component Credit Risk [0.65, 0.85]
component Systemic Risk [0.55, 0.58]
component Cybersecurity Risk [0.55, 0.53]
component Cascade Failure Risk [0.50, 0.50]
component Third-Party Risk [0.50, 0.52]

// Shaping forces (regulation, rating, sovereignty) — sit below risks they cover
component Regulation [0.42, 0.45]
component Rating Agencies [0.55, 0.43]
component Sovereignty Concerns [0.30, 0.40]

// Evolution-axis concepts the user asked about
component Cost [0.40, 0.88]
component Value [0.40, 0.60]
component Supply-Chain Awareness [0.28, 0.28]

// Accountability chain back to society
component Accountability [0.20, 0.45]
component Society [0.10, 0.15]

